message.content: This question requires an understanding of the states of matter and their density. Gold is a solid, which means its particles are closely packed together. Gas, on the other hand, has particles that are spread out and not tightly packed. Wood is also a solid, but it typically has a less dense structure compared to gold. Water is a liquid, and while its particles are closer together than gas, they are not as tightly packed as the particles in gold. Therefore, option (A) - gold - would have more tightly packed matter compared to the other options.
